        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 2:08PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 208 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Yosemite Valley, or 23 miles north of Yosemite South
Entrance, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hetch Hetchy, Hetch Hetchy Ranger Station, Porcupine Flat Campground,
White Wolf Campground, Yosemite Creek Campground, Mather Ranger
Station, and Rancheria Falls Wilderness Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
